title: Grateful Dead Live at Three Rivers Stadium on 1990-07-08
lineage: mac > Yamaha K-98 > Edirol R09 HR > 24/48 wav > Adobe Audition 1.5 > Wavelab 6 (with iZotope Ozone 4) > iZotope RX Advanced > 16/44.1 wav > CD Wave > TLH > Flac 16 taped from OTS, and transferred by John Bleich
description:
Set 1

Touch Of Gray-> Greatest Story Ever Told, Jack A Roe, Minglewood Blues, Row Jimmy, Mama Tried-> Mexicali Blues, Just Like Tom Thumb's Blues, Let It Grow

Set 2

Samson & Delilah-> Eyes Of The World-> Estimated Prophet-> Terrapin Station-> Jam-> Drums-> Jam-> I Need A Miracle-> Wang Dang Doodle-> Black Peter-> Throwing Stones-> Turn On Your Love Light, E: Knockin' On Heaven's Door

Crosby Stills & Nash Opened

reviews.review_text: I was here! I remember it clearly. We drove down to Pittsburgh on this Sunday afternoon. Arrived around 4 pm and partied in the lot till the show started. I dropped 4 hits of acid and walked into the show with my friends. Good times remembered.
